Senator Dino Melaye representing Kogi West Senatorial district has been sacked by the Kogi State National Assembly/State Assembly Election Petition Tribunal.<img class="size-full wp-image-979347 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Dino.png?resize=312%2C280&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="312" height="280" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Dino.png?w=312&amp;ssl=1 312w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Dino.png?resize=300%2C269&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Dino.png?resize=58%2C52&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Dino.png?resize=216%2C194&amp;ssl=1 216w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Dino.png?resize=145%2C130&amp;ssl=1 145w" sizes="(max-width: 312px) 100vw, 312px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Melaye (PDP) was declared winner in the February election by INEC, but Senator Smart Adeyemi (APC)challenged the victory at   the tribunal, alleging irregularities, over voting and non compliance with the electoral acts. Tribunal assures of fair ruling in C’ River gov election petition case(Opens in a new browser tab) The three man panel led by Justice A. O. Chijioke in a unanimous judgment on Friday accepted Adeyemi’s ground and ordered a reelection into the senatorial axis. Senator Melaye is the flamboyant supporter of former Senate President Bukola Saraki from Kwara. Both were originally members of the APC when the party came into power in 2015 but soon fell out with the leadership of APC that opposed the emergence of Saraki as Senate President. Sonorous Senator Melaye was noted for high drama  in and out the Senate. When he was not waxing songs and dancing to deride the opposition, he was at war with his state governor or the police authorities over sundry allegations. Both Senators Dino Melaye and Smart Adeyemi chaired the Senate Committee on the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). Read also :Smart Adeyemi’s emergence shows a united Okun people- Fanwo(Opens in a new browser tab)  Details shortly… Vanguard The gubernatorial election tribunal in Kogi state has, on Friday, sacked Senator Dino Melaye as the senator representing Kogi west district. August 23, 2019 In "News" Irked by the Kogi State National Assembly/State Assembly Election Petition Tribunal judgment, the senator representing Kogi West Senatorial district, Dino Melaye on Friday said he would appeal the case and get judgment at the Appeal Court. August 23, 2019 In "News" The National Assembly and Legislative Houses Election Petition Tribunal sitting in Lokoja, Kogi State has upheld the election of Senator Dino Melaye as the winner of the 2015 Kogi West Senatorial Election against the petition by his rival, Senator Smart Adeyemi. Melaye had been declared winner of the election conducted March… October 12, 2015 In "News"